# Go backend (Cursor backend)

## Layout

- **`main.go`** — Only boot the CLI: call public `Execute()` from `cmd` (no business logic).
- **`cmd/`** — Cobra: one file per command; thin wiring (flags → `pkg`).
- **`cmd/root.go`** — Root command: global setup before any subcommand (config, logging, viper/env, persistent pre-run).
- **`pkg/`** — All logic and domain packages.

## RPC-oriented package files

Per bounded area, prefer: **`rpc.go`** (RPC-facing interface), **`service.go`** (implements RPC), **`repo.go`** (repository interface), **`sql.go`** (concrete repo), **`nop.go`** (identity decorator). Use domain-named dirs when you have several services; keep the same split.

### RPC method shape

Every method on the RPC-facing interface must use **context**, a **single input struct**, a **single output struct**, and **`error`**:

```go
type Service interface {
	SomeMethod(context.Context, SomeMethodInput) (SomeMethodOutput, error)
}
```

Name input/output types after the method (`FooInput` / `FooOutput`). Do not use bare primitives or many positional parameters on the RPC surface.

### `nop.go` — `NopService`

Every RPC package must expose a **`NopService`** in **`nop.go`**: a pass-through wrapper with a **`Next Service`** field so other decorators can embed or compose it. One method per RPC method, delegating to `Next`:

```go
type NopService struct {
	Next Service
}

func (svc NopService) SomeMethod(ctx context.Context, input SomeMethodInput) (SomeMethodOutput, error) {
	return svc.Next.SomeMethod(ctx, input)
}
```

Use this as the base when adding logging, metrics, auth, etc., without re-listing every method from scratch.

## Accept interfaces, return structs

- **Parameters:** depend on **small interfaces** (repos, clocks, etc.) for testability and swapping implementations.
- **Returns:** prefer **concrete structs** from code you own (constructors, internal factories).

```go
func NewService(r TokenRepository) *Service { ... }

type TokenRepository interface {
    Save(ctx context.Context, t Token) error
}
```

Avoid returning a broad interface from `New*` unless you truly need that at a stable public API boundary.

## Compile-time interface checks

Whenever a concrete type implements an interface, add a **blank assignment** next to that type (same file as the implementation) so drift breaks the build:

```go
var _ Service = (*authzService)(nil)
```

Use **`(*T)(nil)`** for **pointer-receiver** implementations. For **value-receiver** types, use **`var _ Service = NopService{}`** (or the zero value of `T`).

## Checklist

- [ ] `main.go` → `Execute()` only; startup in `cmd/root.go`.
- [ ] RPC area: `rpc` / `service` / `repo` / `sql` / `nop` (`NopService` → `Next`); RPC methods `(ctx, XxxInput) (XxxOutput, error)`.
- [ ] **Take interfaces, return structs** at service/repo and similar injection points.
- [ ] `var _ Interface = (*Concrete)(nil)` (or `Concrete{}` for value receivers) for each interface implementation.
